    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Variable Geometry Turbocharger
        (VGT) - Illustration and Description
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Illustration and Description</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <figure id="f3350004125" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk15/k15010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 Spiralock&#174; nut (4)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger mounting gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Compressor outlet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply port</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbine inlet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil drain port</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT actuator</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Compressor inlet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT actuator harness</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT actuator linkage</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 serrated lock nut (4)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">E-clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbine outlet</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The VGT uses actuated vanes mounted on a unison ring inside the turbine housing to modify exhaust gas
                flow to control intake boost pressure for various engine speed and load conditions.
            </para>
            <para>The VGT is part of a closed loop system which uses the Exhaust Back Pressure (EBP) sensor to
                continuously provide exhaust pressure feedback to the ECM.
            </para>
            <para>The Electronic Control Module (ECM) commands the VGT actuator with a digital signal over the CAN 2
                link. A DC motor in the VGT actuator moves linkage connected to the unison ring to control vane position
                and turbocharger boost.
            </para>
            <para>See
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_10.xml" xrefid="s0111">Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT)</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0111"/>
                for additional details.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
